rComments: 369's been great, fun and informative. Many thanks to Larry for making it that way.

Larry is my favorite CSC prof at UTM. His assignments are not unrealistically difficult (unlike other profs, oh boy) and he's just such a nice guy. I hope they keep him on our campus. I did well in a CSC course for once because of him. I always thought I was just horrible at CSC until I took a course with him.
I took OS (369) with him at UTM. He's an awesome prof--approachable, organized, and tries to make lectures engaging.
The only prof who could keep me awake in 3 hour evening classes. Makes AWESOME slides. Very approachable.

Larry's very through when explaining difficult topics and provides plenty of examples to clarify. Our lectures were long (T6-9) but he was funny and engaging. The assignments were manageable (office hours were VERY helpful) as were the midterms.
